===Military===
As the largest single known polity in the Galaxy, the Imperium maintains a wide array of military forces. At any given times there are countless billions fighting for the Imperium of Man. Similar to its political organization each branch of the Imperiumâ€™s military is independent, with their own duties, rituals, chain of command, tactical acumen and gear of war. Though diverse, the forces of the Imperium often work in conjunction with each other, and the larger the battle, the more likely it will be to see multiple Imperial factions engaged in the same war. Massive conflagrations, such as the [[Chaos]] invasions known as the [[Black Crusade]]s or a major war zone such as the one surrounding the planet [[Armageddon]], will attract representatives from all of Mankindâ€™s military institutions.{{Fn|13}}

The military forces of the Imperium consist of:
*[[Planetary Defense Forces]] â€” Often abbreviated to '''PDFs'''. These are independent armies raised and commanded by the Governors of individual Imperial worlds. Though poorly trained and equipped compared to the rest of the Imperium's forces, they serve as the first line of defense.{{Fn|13}}
*The [[Imperial Guard]] â€” The largest single military arm of the Imperium, consisting of vast armies of unaugmented human [[Guardsmen]]. It falls under the control of the [[Administratum]]'s Departmento Munitorum.{{Fn|13}}
**The [[Ordo Tempestus]] â€” Elite forces of the [[Departmento Munitorum]]{{citethis}}
*The [[Imperial Navy]] â€” The military branch of the [[Imperial Fleet]]. Consists of large warfleets of spacecraft tasked with not only space combat but also transporting the [[Imperial Guard]].{{Fn|13}}
**The [[Aeronautica Imperialis]] â€” Atmospheric warfare branch of the Imperial Navy{{citethis}}
*The [[Space Marines]] â€” Elite genetically modified warriors divided into independent armies known as [[Chapter]]s.{{Fn|13}}
*The [[Sisters of Battle]] â€” The all-female military arm of the Imperial church, the [[Ecclesiarchy]].{{Fn|13}}
*The military forces of the [[Adeptus Mechanicus]], which include:
**The [[Collegia Titanica]] â€” Operates Legions of titantic warmachines known as [[Imperial Titan|Titan]]s{{Fn|13}}
**The [[Legiones Skitarii]] â€” Cybernetic soldiers that act as the standing armies of [[Forge World]]s.{{Fn|13}}
**Other miscellaneous smaller and specialized armed wings including the [[Electro-Priest|Electro-Priesthood]], [[Legio Cybernetica]], [[Ordo Reductor]], [[Auxilia Myrmidon]], [[Centurio Ordinatus]], and [[Basilikon Astra|Fleet]]. These are often deployed together in formations known as [[Cult Mechanicus Battle Congregation|Battle Congregations]].{{Fn|15}}
*The [[Imperial Knights]], which include [[Knight House|Houses]] sworn to the [[Adeptus Terra]] or Adeptus Mechanicus.{{Fn|36a}}
**[[Knight Household Guard]] - Support militia of Knight Houses.{{Fn|36a}}
*The [[Sisters of Silence]] â€” [[Psyker]]-hunters of the [[Adeptus Astra Telepathica]] and guards of the [[League of Black Ships|Black Ships]].{{Fn|13}}
*The [[Adeptus Custodes]] â€” The elite guardians of the [[Emperor]]. For most of the Imperium's history they have remained at the [[Imperial Palace]] but recently have ventured forth on [[Crusade]]s.{{citethis}}
*The forces of the [[Inquisition]] â€” Besides the [[Inquisitor]]s and their [[Inquisitorial Henchmen|retinue]]s, the Inquisition's forces include:{{Fn|13}}
**The [[Grey Knights]] â€” [[Chamber Militant]] of the [[Ordo Malleus]]{{citethis}}
**The [[Deathwatch]] â€” Chamber Militant of the [[Ordo Xenos]]{{citethis}}
**The [[Sisters of Battle]] â€” Chamber Militant of the [[Ordo Hereticus]]{{citethis}}
**[[Inquisitorial Stormtrooper]]s - Standard soldiers which act as the guards and enforcers of the Inquisition.
**Independent fleet assets which include [[Inquisitorial Black Ship]]s and [[Inquisitorial Cruiser]]s.{{citethis}}
*The [[Arbitrator]]s - The armed wing of the [[Adeptus Arbites]], the Imperium's police force. Heavy armed and equipped, they often see combat during issues of planetary invasion and rebellions.{{Fn|14}}
*The [[Officio Assassinorum]] â€” Agency which deploys specialized deadly assassins.{{Fn|13}}
*The [[Praeses Mercatura]] - armed wing of the [[Merchant Fleet]].{{Fn|21}}
*The [[Literati]] - Armed guards and enforcers of the [[Administratum]].{{Fn|26e}}
*The [[Black Sentinels]] - Guardians of facilities of the [[Adeptus Astra Telepathica]]{{Fn|37}}.
*[[Astynomia]] - Security force of [[Adeptus Mechanicus]] [[Forge World]]s.{{Fn|30b}}
*[[Frateris Militia]] â€” ad hoc militias raised by the [[Ecclesiarchy]] during [[Wars of Faith]].{{citethis}}

Former military forces of the Imperium include:
*The [[Legiones Astartes]] â€” The original organization of the [[Space Marine]]s which saw them divided into twenty [[Space Marine Legion|Legion]]s each led by a [[Primarch]].{{citethis}}
*The [[Imperial Army]] â€” The largest military force of the early Imperium, split into the [[Imperial Guard]] and [[Imperial Navy]] after the [[Horus Heresy]].{{citethis}}
**The [[Solar Auxilia]] â€” The fighting elite of the Imperial Army.{{citethis}}
**The [[Imperialis Militia]] â€” Auxiliaries analogous to modern PDFs.{{citethis}}
**The [[Imperialis Armada]] â€” Naval branch reorganized into the Imperial Navy after the Horus Heresy.{{citethis}}
*The [[Taghmata Omnissiah]] â€” Type of organizational command for [[Mechanicus]] forces, roughly analogous to [[Cult Mechanicus Battle Congregation]]s.
*The [[Frateris Templar]] â€” Large standing army of the [[Ecclesiarchy]]. Replaced by the [[Sisters of Battle]] after the [[Age of Apostasy]].
*The [[Order Elucidatum]] - The secret police of [[Malcador the Sigillite]].
*The [[Thunder Warriors]] â€” The earliest known genetically modified supersoldiers of the Imperium. Were led by the [[Emperor]] himself in the [[Unification Wars]]. Replaced by the Legiones Astartes
