{{AgesImperium}}
'''The Age of Rebirth''' was the time that followed the events of the disastrous [[Horus Heresy]]. It is the first era of the [[Age of the Imperium]]. The damage to the [[Imperium]] was slowly repaired and its military forces reformed to secure safety. Eventually, it was not a military conflict that would revive unrest but a massive assassination attempt.{{Fn|1}}

==Events==
===The Great Scouring (.M31)===
{{Main|Great Scouring}}
The Imperium survived the [[Horus Heresy]], but only just. With the [[Emperor]] confined to the [[Golden Throne]] it was leaderless and the Followers of [[Chaos]] were still spread throughout the galaxy. A campaign of vengeance was started to reclaim lost territories, driving the forces of the traitors into the [[Eye of Terror]] and reestablishing stability.{{Fn|1}}{{Fn|2}}

===The Codex Astartes===
{{Main|Codex Astartes}}
Various doctrines and edicts were drawn up to prevent a large-scale military rebellion such as the Horus Heresy from ever happening again. The most notable of them was the Codex Astartes which split the remaining [[Space Marine Legion]]s into smaller, more numerous [[Chapter]]s.{{Fn|1}}

===The Beast (544.M32)===
{{Main|War of the Beast}}
In 544.[[M32]] an [[Ork]] [[Warboss]] known only as [[The Beast]] united much of the Ork race and nearly succeeded in conquering the [[Galaxy]]. His [[Waaagh!]] was the largest the Galaxy has ever seen and rampaged across the [[Imperium]]. The Imperium only halted his advance at great cost and desperate measure, devastating the [[Adeptus Astartes]].{{Fn|3}}

===The Beheading (546.M32)===
{{Main|The Beheading}}
[[Drakan Vangorich]], [[Grand Master of Assassins|Grand Master]] of the [[Officio Assassinorum]] initiated the deaths of the [[High Lords of Terra]] and in return was slain by the single survivor of a retribution force drawn from the [[Halo Brethren]], [[Imperial Fists]] and [[Sable Swords]] [[Chapter]]s. In the aftermath, the [[Imperium]] descended into anarchy.{{Fn|1}}

