{{Ambig|subject=Imperial symbol|disambiguation=Aquila}}

The '''Aquila'''{{Fn|1a}} (plural: ''Aquilae''{{Fn|10}}) (also known as '''Imperial Aquila''' {{Fn|5}}, '''great Aquila'''{{Fn|15}} and '''Imperial Eagle'''{{Fn|2}}) normally{{Fn|29}}{{Fn|Note 1}} refers to a two-headed eagle{{Fn|1a}}{{Fn|3}} that symbolizes the [[Pax Imperialis]], the oath that binds together all [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperial]] servants under the banner of the [[Emperor of Mankind]]{{Fn|2}}. It is a universal symbol within the Imperium and
more than anything else represents the dominion of the Emperor.{{Fn|29}} It is also said that the Eagle and its variations symbolize both the Imperium as such and also loyalty to the Emperor as its master.{{Fn|8}} It also is the heraldic device of the [[Adeptus Terra|Imperial state]] and at the same time holy symbol of the [[Imperial Cult]].{{Fn|10}} The double-headed eagle also represents the union of the [[Mechanicum]] of [[Mars]] and the Emperor{{Fn|12a}} or between Mars and [[Terra]]{{Fn|14}}.
[[Image:Imperial Eagle.jpg|right|thumb|300px|The ''Aquila'', symbol of the [[Imperium of Mankind]]{{Fn|3}}]]

==History==
===Pre-Great Crusade===
Before the formalisation of the ''Eagle'' (also see [[Raptor Imperialis]]) as the symbol of the [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperium]] the [[Emperor of Mankind|Emperor]]'s personal device was the [[Thunderbolt and lightning]] emblem which was used during the [[Unification Wars]].{{Fn|11f}} But the ''Imperial Eagle'' also is a symbol of the Emperor's ''War of Unification''.{{Fn|14}}

