==Design and meanings==
The ''Aquila'' most commonly{{Fn|29}} has two heads looking into different directions{{Fn|29}}, one said blinded to look at the past, one sighted to see to the future{{Fn|1a}} or one head gazing into the ''Materium'' while the other gazes into the ''[[Immaterium]]''{{Fn|29}}. Other sources associate the blind head with the [[Adeptus Astronomica]]{{Fn|6}}{{Fn|10}} and the seeing head with the [[Adeptus Astra Telepathica]]{{Fn|10}}{{Fn|Conflicting sources}}.

[[File:AquilaBedeutung.jpg|thumb|center|300px|The ''Aquila''{{Fn|6}}]]


The left wing (as seen from the viewer's perspective) represents the [[Adeptus Astra Telepathica]]{{Fn|6}}{{Fn|Conflicting sources}} while the right wing represents the [[Adeptus Mechanicus]]{{Fn|6}}{{Fn|10}}. The Eagle's body stands for the [[Adeptus Custodes]]{{Fn|6}}{{Fn|10}}, while the left, straight claw (again as seen from the viewer's perspective) represents the [[Administratum]] and the right, crooked claw the [[Adeptus Arbites]].{{Fn|6}}{{Fn|10}}

==Usage==
The device of the ''Aquila'' is generally used throughout the galaxy wherever the [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperium]] wishes to proclaim its authority.{{Fn|10}} Typical examples include architecture{{Fn|12c}}, armour, vehicles (like space ships{{Fn|1c}}{{Fn|31a}}{{Fn|31b}}), weapons, containers{{Fn|1d}} etc.{{Fn|10}} and - at least prior to the [[Horus Heresy]] - also currency, i.e. on coins{{Fn|11a}}:
*''Aquilae'' are frequently worn by [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperial]] servants, for example on clothing, ceremonial dresses, armour or in the form of jewelry (for example as a necklace{{Fn|12d}}{{Fn|12e}} or as a brooch{{Fn|16}}), tattoos{{Fn|12b}}{{Fn|15}} (or as etchings across shoulder blades{{Fn|1b}}) or other adornments.{{Fn|10}}


