==Sign of the Aquila==
The ''Sign of the Aquila'' (often shortened to simply ''Aquila'') is a sign of devotion to the [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperium]]{{Fn|4}} also used for example as a sign of defiance against [[Warp entity|Warp entities]]{{Fn|11c}}. It was used a sign of devotion from early on{{Fn|1e}}. It is also known to have been used as a formal greeting between at least [[Space Marines]]{{Fn|11b}} and as a sign of respect towards fallen brothers{{Fn|11d}}.

Descriptions of how to actually do this sign are however a bit unclear: In one instance it is said that hands are placed or pressed to one's chest, palms open, blades of fingers extended and thumbs raised{{Fn|1f}} while others say and show the thumbs are interlocked or crossed{{Fn|4}}{{Fn|9}}{{Fn|15}} while yet another source says the "fingers" are "laced" into the shape on an ''Aquila''{{Fn|17}}.

[[File:Signoftheaquila.jpg|thumb|center|150px|The ''Sign of the Aquila''{{Fn|9}}]]

==Other information==
*Soldiers of the [[Imperial Guard]] are obliged to salute (amongst others) any image of the ''Aquila'' - failure to do so is punished by being branded on the left cheek and a court-martial.{{Fn|7}}
*When no proper altar to the [[Emperor of Mankind]] is available one can be improvised by [[Imperial Guard]] officers to conduct their ceremonies: under certain circumstances and at certain times an ''Aquila'' standard is suspended from a wall and a yellow chalk cross on the floor beneath it then marks the sacred spot.{{Fn|18}}
*At least servants of the [[Ecclesiarchy]] are expected to make the ''Sign of the Aquila'' when facing an Ecclesiarchical shrine or when seeing a sign of [[Chaos|the Ruinous Powers]].{{Fn|9}} Making the sign to honour altars also is a known practice amongst other Imperial servants.{{Fn|30}}
*''Aquila'' devices have been known to become the focus of tangible manifestations of religious power.{{Fn|10}}{{Fn|12e}}
*At least prior to the [[Horus Heresy]]{{Fn|11e}} it was considered a "great crime" to damage the ''Imperial Eagle'' on the chestplate of the [[Emperor's Children]].{{Fn|11e}}

