==Trivia==
{{trivia}}

''Aquila'' simply is the [[Wikipedia:Aquila|Latin and Romance languages word for eagle]].

Double-headed eagles are or have been used in many different contexts [[Wikipedia:Double-headed eagle|throughout history]]: "In heraldry and vexillology, the double-headed eagle (or double-eagle) is a charge associated with the concept of ''Empire''. Most modern uses of the symbol are directly or indirectly associated with its use by the [[Wikipedia:Byzantine Empire|Byzantine Empire]], whose use of it represented the Empire's dominion over the Near East and the West."

Modern day users of the emblem are as diverse as [[Wikipedia:Albania|Albania]], [[Wikipedia:Serbia|Serbia]], [[Wikipedia:Montenegro|Montenegro]] and [[Wikipedia:Russia|Russia]], the [[Wikipedia:Hellenic Army|Hellenic Army]], different Orthodox Christian Churches and also cities such as [[Wikipedia:Toledo, Spain|Toledo (Spain)]], [[Wikipedia:Velletri|Velletri (Italy)]], [[Wikipedia:Rijeka|Rijeka (Croatia)]] or [[Wikipedia:Konya|Konya (Turkey)]] to name but a few.

===Notes===
===={{Endn|Note 1}}====
Since the word ''Aquila'' simply means "eagle" special attention should be paid to the exact context and wording of sources. Sometimes ''Aquila'', ''Eagle'' or ''Imperial Eagle'' might refer to the double-headed symbol, but sometimes it might also denote a normal, one-headed eagle.

===={{Endn|Note 2}}====
Due to the lack of supplies during the [[Horus Heresy]] the different marks of [[Power Armour]] including older ones were used throughout the conflict and even thereafter.{{Fn|26}} In addition older marks came to be associated with the history or past deeds and are therefore still used and much sought after up to current times.{{Fn|26}} Since these images are not precisely dated it is impossible to say if the use of the ''Aquila'' was a constant or temporary feature or when it started.

=={{Endn|Conflicting sources}}==
The image of the ''Aquila'' in [[Warhammer 40,000: Rogue Trader]]{{Fn|6}} relatively clearly shows that the inscription "Adeptus Astra Telepathica" is connected to the left wing and not to the sighted head of the eagle. But [[The Inquisition (Background Book)]]{{Fn|10}} unequivocally states that when "depicted in correct detail" the sighted head represents the "Adeptus Astra Telepathica". Therefore it could be assumed that the image in ''Rogue Trader'' is incorrect. But on the other hand ''The Inquisition'' does not mention the left wing at all.{{Fn|10}}

