{{ImperiumPortal}}
'''''Civitas Imperialis''''' is an [[Imperial]] term most simply translated as ''"the Imperial rule of law,"'' although its true meaning is more specific. When the [[Imperium of Man]] was founded, the ''Civitas'' was laid down to ''"guarantee the safety and assurance of any citizen of the Imperium of Mankind, wherever he or she travels or sets foot within the length and breadth of the Imperium."''{{Fn|1c}} The ''Civitas'' was thus an implicit promise to the Imperium's citizens of justice and the protection of the Imperium's soldiers and resources.
The ''Civitas Imperialis'' was officially suspended in the [[Sabbat Worlds]] in 741.[[M41]], a final acknowledgment that the [[sector]] had been lost to the forces of [[Chaos]].{{Fn|1a}} Part of [[Lord Militant]] [[Slaydo]]'s remit from the [[High Lords of Terra]], as the newly-appointed [[Warmaster]] of the [[Sabbat Worlds Crusade]], was to restore the ''Civitas Imperialis'' to that region.{{Fn|1b}} From his diaries, historians have concluded that Slaydo was determined to do so, within the fullest meaning of the term.{{Fn|1c}}
== Sources == *1: [[The Sabbat Worlds Crusade (Background Book)]] by [[Dan Abnett]] **{{Endn|1a}}: pg. 5 **{{Endn|1b}}: pg. 12 **{{Endn|1c}}: pg. 13
[[Category:Imperium]] [[Category:Imperial Texts]] [[Category:Sabbat Worlds Crusade]]

{{ImperiumPortal}}
'''Clan Bannick''' is one of the [[Noble House|clan families]] of the [[sixth moon of Paragon VI]].{{Fn|1b}}

The clan's main industry was in opticals.{{Fn|1f}}

==History==
At one point, Clan Bannick was to be tied to [[Clan Turannigen]] by the marriage of [[Colaron Vor Artem Lo Bannick|Colaron Bannick]] (son of his clan's Chief Auditor) and [[Kaithalar Beyn Lo Turannigen|Kaithalar Turannigen]] (her clan's Warden). However, after Colaron killed his cousin, [[Tuparillio]], in an honour duel, he enlisted with the [[Astra Militarum]] as penance and the marriage was consequently called off.{{Fn|1b}}{{Fn|1c}} This led to Clan Bannick suffering a 0.3% gross reduction in interclan trade and Colaron was effectively disowned by his father and most of the clan.{{Fn|1b}} 

