{{ImperiumPortal}}
'''Clan Habeyl''' was once the [[Imperial Commander|ruling]] [[Imperial House]] of the [[Hive World]] [[Garmesh]].{{Fn|1}}
==History==
They had ruled there for many generations, but the string of Habeyl rulers proved to be incompetent and aided in [[Garmesh]]'s decline. This caused the [[Hive World]] to lose its position as the beating heart of the [[Mathenda Sub-sector]] and resulted in Garmesh's population languishing in poverty, while its indolent [[Imperial Commander]]s hid in their [[Hive Spire|Spire Fortresses]] and ignored their plight. The latest head of the Clan, [[Habeyl VII]] was no different, but in [[M42]] the resentment towards him, led nine [[Unsanctioned Psyker]]s of Garmesh' population to form a [[Seercult|cabal]], within its [[Underhive]]. They had done so after listening to a voice in visions they received as they were dreaming, which the cabal believed was the [[Emperor]]. This voice bade them to pool their powers together to save Garmesh and the cabal called itself the [[Heralds of Change]], and set about mounting a sorcerous insurrection upon the Hive World.{{Fn|1}}  

[[Habeyl VII]] would not take their threat seriously until it was too late and the [[Heralds of Change|Heralds]] began to threaten his rule of [[Garmesh]]. He would send out [[astropathic]] pleas for aid and to be evacuated, before then joining his fellow [[Noble]]s in hiding within their [[Hive Spire]] fortresses. There, they would wait in safety as the Noble's household guards held back the [[Seercult|cabal]]'s onslaught, until help could arrive to defeat the cabal. Once the Heralds learned of this, they became desperate and with victory so close at hand, the cabal beseeched the [[God-Emperor]] to aid them. However it was not the Emperor, but the [[Lord of Change]] [[Tz'Keth'K'Zar]] who answered their plea. It was the [[Greater Daemon]] who had been speaking to them in their visions and was all to pleased to aid them. Once the Lord of Change materialized upon Garmesh, the Heralds were turned into a [[Warp Gate]], through which the legions of [[Tzeentch]] invaded the Hive World. It would then be enveloped by the [[Chaos God]]'s power, though sometime later the [[Imperial Navy]] [[Frigate]] [[Hopeful Saint]] arrived to evacuate Habeyl. Its crew was stunned by the Hive World's fate and the warship's [[Shipmaster|Shipmistress]] [[Endara]], was also unable to make contact with the [[Imperial Commander]]. Before she could decide on what to do next, Tzeentch Daemons invaded the Hopeful Saint and set its bridge aflame with [[Warp]]fire.{{Fn|1}}

