The '''Great Exodus''' was an event in [[Imperial]] history, occurring in 750.[[M41]].{{Fn|1}}
[[Eldar]] forces consisting of six entire [[Craftworld]]s appeared in the [[Argos System]] and vanished with a mysterious swirling celestial phenomenon previously seen in the area. The event extinguished all suns within sixty light years, threatening [[human]] worlds. The [[Imperial Fleet]], [[Imperial Navy]], and other innumerable transports undertook a vast evacuation of the System, transporting billions of citizens and infrastructure. It is estimated that 12% of the population and 32% of the heavy industry in the System were safely transported. The ring of dead planets has since become known as the [[Deadhenge]], a salvager's paradise and refuge for pirates.{{Fn|1}}
