'''Imperium Eterna''' is the name given by [[Terran]] [[Imperial]]s to the previous state of the [[Imperium]], before it was heavily changed by [[Lord Commander]] [[Guilliman]].{{Fn|1a}} 

Those who do so, yearn to undo [[Guilliman]]'s work, as they consider ''Imperium Eterna'' to be a perfect realm whose [[Lex Imperialis]] reflected the [[Emperor]]'s will. They claim the damning changes wrought by Guilliman, ruined the [[Emperor of Mankind|Emperor]]'s design and protest that the [[Lord Commander]]'s [[Indomitus Crusade]] continues to bleed [[Terra]] of its resources and defenders. More strikingly some feel that the Lord Commander has ignored the [[Great Rift|violent strife that still rivets]] Terra, as he is instead more concerned with thousands of other worlds. Guilliman's most damning [[Irthu Haemotalion|critics]] state that restoring ''Imperium Eterna'' would have the [[Imperium of Mankind|Imperium]] ruled once more by [[High Lords|mortals]] and not uncaring [[Primarch]]s who are far removed from Terra's turmoil.{{Fn|1b}}

