==Sources== *1: [[Vaults of Terra: The Hollow Mountain (Novel)]] **{{Endn|1a}}: Chapter 7 **{{Endn|1b}}: Chapter 9 **{{Endn|1c}}: Chapter 10 **{{Endn|1d}}: Chapter 6 [[Category:Imperium]]

{{ImperiumPortal}}
Imperial '''Iterators''' were public speakers, and masters of manipulating crowds and altering public opinion. The [[Emperor of Mankind|Emperor]] appointed them to spread the [[Imperial Truth]] among his people, for example the rejection of the religions and petty squabbling which had brought about the [[Age of Strife]].{{Fn|1}}

They were most prevalent among the fleets of the [[Great Crusade]], where they would not only lecture and rally the Imperial troops and [[Astartes]] legions, but also educate the vanquished human civilisations on the values and virtues of the [[Imperium]].{{Fn|1}}

[[Warmaster]] [[Horus]] admired the Iterators' work, so much that he asked them to also tutor his Captains and Legionaries; Horus believed that, once the Crusade was completed, there would be an end to war and the [[Astartes]] would need to find a peacetime vocation.{{Fn|1}}

The most famous iterator of the [[Great Crusade]] was Primary Iterator [[Kyril Sindermann]], who served aboard Horus's flagship, the ''[[Vengeful Spirit]]'' at the head of the [[63rd Expeditionary Fleet]].{{Fn|1}}


