{{ImperiumPortal}}
'''Life-Sellers''' were [[Horus Heresy]]-era [[Imperials]] on [[Terra]], who sold their lives dearly defending the [[Siege of Terra|besieged]] [[Imperial Palace]], after being unable or unwilling to enter the [[Eternity Gate]] before it closed.{{Fn|1d}}
==History==
Those that remained outside the last bastion of the [[Imperium]]'s territory, had no hope of receiving reinforcements and were left to fight on against the overwhelming hordes of [[Horus]]' forces. Among them was the [[Blood Angel]] [[Khotus Meffiel]], who first spoke of the term Life-Seller to the [[White Scar]] [[Zhintas Khan]]. In his mind, their deaths were now inevitable and the Imperials fighting outside of the [[Eternity Gate]] had one goal left to them: To sell their lives dearly and see how many Traitors they could kill, before death claimed them.{{Fn|1d}}

