{{ImperialKnightsPortal}}
{{redirect|Becoming|the short story by [[Andy Clark]]|Becoming (Short Story)}}
The '''Ritual of Becoming''' is a key event in the training of an [[Imperial Knight]].{{Fn|1}}

When a Noble of a [[Knight House]] reaches their 18th year, they must undergo the Ritual of Becoming, an event that is viewed with great honour and solemnity.  Inside the house's sanctuary, they are connected to one of the vacant [[Throne Mechanicum]].  They are then left, typically for a full night, alone.  The young aspirant must wrestle with the energies of the Throne Mechanicum, attempting to imprint their psyche upon it without being overwhelmed by its cerebral engrams in turn.  Sometimes the process is enough to drive the aspirant mad, other times they are killed outright.  Those who survive are forever changed, their childhood left behind and the mantle of knighthood now resting heavily upon their shoulders.{{Fn|1}}

==Sources==
*{{Endn|1}}: [[Codex: Imperial Knights (8th Edition)]], pg. 7

[[Category:Adeptus Mechanicus]]
[[Category:Imperium]]

{{NecromundaPortal}}{{AdeptusMechanicusPortal}}{{ImperiumPortal}} '''Rogue Factoria''' are [[Imperial]] factories that are used by criminal organizations to create counterfeit weaponry and wargear.{{Fn|1a}} ==Description== Though the counterfeits are cheaply produced, selling them is a very lucrative enterprise for criminals. Rogue Factoria also have the added benefit of keeping their owners' allies well-equipped with ordnance{{Fn|1a}}. They are overseen by '''Factoria Overseers''', with '''Work Party Bosses''' charged with overseeing the '''Factoria Workers''' who create the counterfeit goods. These workers are motley groups of miscreants, that are gathered from wherever their Rogue Factoria masters can find them. On [[Hive Worlds]], some are criminals who work in the Rogue Factoria, in order to pay off their debts to their [[Underhive]] criminal bosses. Others are escapes from Uphive, who had sought freedom and wealth, but instead found a new life that was much like their old one. When the owners of the Rogue Factoria need to help their allies or defend their Factoria, they will arm a group of Workers, with cast-off weaponry, and send them into battle. This ad hoc militia, known as a '''Factoria Work Gang''', is led by a Factoria Overseer, with a Work Party Boss serving as their second in command. However the life of Factoria Worker is of little consequence to the Rogue Factoria's criminal owners. As a result, they are considered expendable and will be used as fodder to protect the Rogue Factoria. The Workers can also be loaned out to serve as expendable troops in the battles of the owners' allies{{Fn|1b}}. The [[Adeptus Mechanicus]] is also always on the look out, for those who create and use counterfeit [[Imperial]] goods.{{Fn|1a}}
==Necromunda== On [[Necromunda (planet)|Necromunda]], Rogue Factorias are used by the more nefarious elements of [[House Cawdor]]. These natural scavengers and notorious misers make great use of the Factoria's counterfeit goods. However just like on other [[Imperial]] worlds, the eye of the [[Adeptus Mechanicus]] is own Necromunda. Those found using a Rogue Factoria's goods will find that the [[Hive World]]'s [[Guilders]] have placed a bounty on their heads, for the Mechanicus.{{Fn|1a}}
==Sources== *1: [[Necromunda: House of Faith]] **{{Endn|1a}}: pg. 83 - ''Strong Alliances: Rogue Factoria'' **{{Endn|1b}}: pg. 88 - ''Strong Alliances: Factoria Work Gangs''
