{{LOVPortal}}{{ImperiumPortal}}
The ''' Rumour Engine''' was an [[Imperial]] [[cogitator]] that created small images, that were glimpses into the future.{{Fn|1}}
==History==
Those who have seen it, claim the Rumour Engine bears a startling resemblance to the [[League of Votann]]'s [[Ancestor Cores]], including having bearded faces that have been carved into the [[cogitator]]'s sides{{Fn|2}}. Some even claimed the device was sentient. However the sheer amount of inscrutable future-derived data the cogitator repetitiously assembled, has recently caused the Rumour Engine to break down. The [[Imperium]] has now asked its attendees, known as the [[Many With Eyes]], to split the processing of the Rumour Engine's auguries amongst themselves. They all have been given a routine [[data wafer]] to conduct this task and each is encoded with a possibility of what the future may hold.{{Fn|3}}
==Trivia==
{{Trivia}}
The ''Rumour Engine'' is a feature of [[Warhammer Community]] articles, that offer hints of upcoming miniatures that [[Games Workshop]] will release. The images shown are said to have been displayed by the Rumour Engine itself.{{Fn|1}} 

