{{ImperiumPortal}}
[[Image:ScarAB.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Scar/AB operatives utilizing forbidden [[Xenos]] wargear{{Fn|1}}]] 
The '''Scar/AB''' are a mysterious clandestine [[Imperial]] unit, whose operatives specialize in terror tactics including night attacks, trophy taking and worse.{{Fn|1}} 
==History==
Their motivations for these dire acts remain unknown, as is who or what organization the Scar/AB work for. It is known, however, that the Scar/AB wield [[Imperial]] weapons whose maker's stamps have been filed off and also make use of forbidden [[Xenos]] weapons and technology. The unit is led on their missions by a shadowy woman known as the [[Matriarch Firebrand]], who exhibits an unnatural control over her fellow operatives. Many [[Inquisition]] agents have died trying to learn exactly where the Matriarch gets her orders from.{{Fn|1}}
==Trivia==
{{Trivia}}
The ''Scar/AB'' and the [[Matriarch Firebrand]] were created by the [[Games Workshop]] employee [[Tammy Nicholls]] and they were featured in [[Warhammer: Visions 18]].{{Fn|1}} 
