{{ImperiumPortal}}
The '''Static Tendency''' are a group of [[Imperial]] officials in the [[Imperial Palace]], who resist any efforts to change the Imperium's constitution.{{Fn|1}} 

They viewed it to be perfect, by a clear understanding of historical law and theology, and any attempt to fundamentally change the constitution, amounted to treason against the [[Emperor]] Himself. When the reborn [[Primarch]] [[Guilliman]] returned to Terra, he began efforts to weaken the Static Tendency; as he realized they would stand in the way of the changes he sought to make to the [[Imperium]]. Chief amongst these efforts, was the removal of any [[High Lords]] that were part of the Static Tendency, which included [[Irthu Haemotalion]] and [[Baldo Slyst]]. However he allowed the Static sympathizers [[Aveliza Drachmar]] and [[Fadix]] to remain as High Lords. In doing so, Guilliman tried to maintain a difficult balancing act, between the various Imperial factions he now had to contend with.{{Fn|1}}

