{{ImperiumPortal}}
The '''Van Skorvold Cartel''' was a mercantile clan active in the [[Geryon Subsector]] that specialised in human trafficking, supplying labour across the subsector for the [[Departmento Munitorum]], the [[Imperial Navy]] and even the [[Adeptus Mechanicus]] (in the form of base stock for the construction of [[Servitor]]s).{{Fn|1a}}  [[Van Skorvold Star Fort|The group's headquarters]] were a converted [[Imperial Space Station|defence platform]] in orbit of the planet [[Lakonia]].{{Fn|1b}}

The cartel's crest was a planet flanked by a pair of stylised human twins.{{Fn|1a}}

At one point the head of the cartel was [[Diego Van Skorvold]].  After his death, leadership of the cartel passed to his offspring, [[Callisthenes Van Skorvold|Callisthenes]] and [[Veritas Van Skorvold]].{{Fn|1a}}

For many years there were rumours that the cartel was engaged in criminal activities, specifically the smuggling of artefacts and illegal [[mutant]]s.  Eventually the persistence of these claims led the [[Administratum|Adeptus Administratum]] to organise a raid on their base of operations, led by [[Consul Senioris]] [[Iocanthos Gullyan Kraevik Chloure|Chloure]].  Although he had support from the Imperial Navy and the Adeptus Mechanicus, Chloure decided to seek the assistance of the [[Space Marines]] to make sure the star fort was taken - to that end, he intentionally leaked information that the cartel had come into possession of a lost relic of the [[Soul Drinkers]] [[Chapter]], an ancient weapon known as the [[Soulspear]].  Sure enough, the Soul Drinkers sent a response force of roughly 300 Marines, led by [[Space Marine Commander|Commander]] [[Caeon]] to seize the station.{{Fn|1a}}

Although Caeon himself was killed during the mission, both Callisthenes and Veritas were captured{{Fn|1a}} and their star fort was destroyed{{Fn|1c}} - the ultimate fate of the cartel is unknown, however.

